name: Decca Records 1951 Speciality Series (set of 6) - The King and I
description:
A Decca Original Cast Album featuring Members of the New York Production
Rodgers and Hammerstein present Gertrude Lawrence in a new musical play "The King and I" with Yul Brynner
Music by Richard Rodgers/Lyrics by Oscar Hammerstein II 
(book no longer included)

with Dorothy Sarnoff, Doretta Morrow, Larry Douglas
Directed by John van Druten
Songs include:
Overture, I whistle a happy tune, My lord and master, Hello, young lovers, March of the Siamese children, A puzzlement, Getting to know you, We kiss in a shadow, Something wonderful, Shall I tell you what I think of you?, I have dreamed, Shall we dance?

Packaging and records in excellent condition. I do not have a record player so cannot confirm if the six records are playable but the quality and condition look very good.

I will send further digital close-up photos for interested buyers.

Copyright 1951

name: Wayang Kulit Indonesian shadow puppet
description:
This is an Indonesian or Bali cowhide/leather hand puppet. It is vintage, thus some of the color overlay has peeled off.

From www.puppetuniverse.com:
Wayang Kulit: an Indonesian form of shadow puppetry commonly performed with the use of leather puppets. This form of theater is directly linked with cultural and historical traditions of the peoples in the Indonesian region. The puppets are created from buffalo hide and attached to wire rods. Wayang Kulit puppets are notable because of the intricacy with which they are carved.

Surf to http://www.murnis.com/articles_by_murni/shadow_puppets.html for more information on this particular shadow puppet.

In fair condition. 

Interested buyers, email me for further pictures of this vintage item.

2 available
